WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.600
[Amit Varma]: There are terms we take for granted that perhaps we need to look at closely. One of them is

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:14.280
[Amit Varma]: art. What is art? How do we define it? Can art only be done by those who have been deemed

00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:19.240
[Amit Varma]: by elites and academics to be artists? Or can anyone do art? Is a five year old kid

00:00:19.240 --> 00:00:24.080
[Amit Varma]: drawing an upside down house and a pink moon creating art? As a guide to thinking about

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:28.800
[Amit Varma]: this, I recommend an excellent book by Ernst Gombrich, The Story of Art, which begins with

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:34.720
[Amit Varma]: these words, quote, There really is no such thing as art. There are only artists. Once

00:00:34.720 --> 00:00:38.440
[Amit Varma]: these were men who took colored earth and roughed out the forms of a bison on the walls

00:00:38.440 --> 00:00:42.960
[Amit Varma]: of a cave. Today they buy their paints and design posters for the underground. They did

00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:47.720
[Amit Varma]: many things in between. There is no harm in calling all these activities art, as long

00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:52.480
[Amit Varma]: as we keep in mind that such a word may mean very different things in different times and

00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:58.280
[Amit Varma]: places. And as long as we realize that art with a capital A has no existence. For art

00:00:58.280 --> 00:01:02.600
[Amit Varma]: with a capital A has come to be something of a bogey and a fetish. You may crush an

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:06.400
[Amit Varma]: artist by telling him that what he has just done may be quite good in its own way, only

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:11.320
[Amit Varma]: it is not art. And you may confound anyone enjoying a picture by declaring that what

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:17.080
[Amit Varma]: he liked in it was not the art, but something different. Stop quote. I agree with Gombrich.

00:01:17.080 --> 00:01:21.720
[Amit Varma]: And I'm glad that we are finally achieving a world in which a small group of elite gatekeepers

00:01:21.720 --> 00:01:26.920
[Amit Varma]: and tastemakers don't get to decide what is art. To hell with them. We don't need them.

00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:31.840
[Amit Varma]: We can all be artists if we want.

