03:58:56.340 --> 03:58:58.660
[Amit Varma]: So NFTs, of course, stand for non fungible token.

03:58:58.660 --> 03:59:01.620
[Guest]: Now, just take it away from there.

03:59:01.620 --> 03:59:03.740
[Guest]: The basic idea, what is non fungible?

03:59:03.740 --> 03:59:05.700
[Guest]: So fungible is like currency.

03:59:05.700 --> 03:59:08.500
[Guest]: Suppose you have a 100 rupee note, you can exchange it for another 100.

03:59:08.500 --> 03:59:10.100
[Amit Varma]: We have a 500 rupee note.

03:59:10.100 --> 03:59:14.060
[Amit Varma]: The 1000 and 500 were demonetized and we had 2000 and new 500.

03:59:14.060 --> 03:59:15.300
[Amit Varma]: Oh, we have new 500?

03:59:15.300 --> 03:59:16.300
[Amit Varma]: We have new 500.

03:59:16.300 --> 03:59:17.300
[Amit Varma]: Oh, I'm sorry.

03:59:17.300 --> 03:59:18.300
[Amit Varma]: I've been out of touch.

03:59:18.300 --> 03:59:19.300
[Guest]: Don't offend me.

03:59:19.300 --> 03:59:20.300
[Guest]: I'm very close to my 500 rupee note.

03:59:20.300 --> 03:59:24.340
[Guest]: So 500 rupee note can be exchanged for any other 500 rupee note for the same value.

03:59:24.340 --> 03:59:26.660
[Guest]: So it is fungible.

03:59:26.660 --> 03:59:30.460
[Guest]: Non fungible token is anything that cannot be exchanged for something just like it.

03:59:30.460 --> 03:59:32.540
[Guest]: It has its own unique value.

03:59:32.540 --> 03:59:38.800
[Guest]: So non fungible tokens have been mostly used in the term of art right now, but they have

03:59:38.800 --> 03:59:40.260
[Guest]: all kinds of uses.

03:59:40.260 --> 03:59:46.580
[Guest]: So a non fungible token can be simply your right to say an artist sells a non fungible

03:59:46.580 --> 03:59:48.780
[Guest]: token for something, something value.

03:59:48.780 --> 03:59:54.560
[Guest]: And now that token gives you the right, it works as a backstage pass to all their concerts.

03:59:54.560 --> 04:00:00.540
[Guest]: As long as you own that token, that NFT and hundreds of people might, you can go to all

04:00:00.540 --> 04:00:05.420
[Guest]: their concerts and you have a special seat and you can always get a backstage entry.

04:00:05.420 --> 04:00:08.100
[Guest]: So that thing does not have the same value always.

04:00:08.100 --> 04:00:09.520
[Guest]: Its value will keep changing.

04:00:09.520 --> 04:00:12.220
[Guest]: If the artist gets better, its value will increase.

04:00:12.220 --> 04:00:16.180
[Guest]: It will be traded by other people like maybe I don't care about this artist anymore.

04:00:16.180 --> 04:00:17.260
[Guest]: Why don't you buy it from me?

04:00:17.260 --> 04:00:21.020
[Guest]: I'll sell it to you for $10 million because now he's the biggest artist in the world.

04:00:21.020 --> 04:00:23.580
[Guest]: So this value is always fluctuating.

04:00:23.580 --> 04:00:26.500
[Guest]: So that's what makes it non fungible.

04:00:26.500 --> 04:00:32.100
[Guest]: Like it's not easily exchangeable for just something, there's no static value to it.

04:00:32.100 --> 04:00:39.460
[Guest]: Now what it rests upon is your notion of the value of digital content in the digital realm.

04:00:39.460 --> 04:00:45.220
[Guest]: Does digital art or a digital product have value in your life?

04:00:45.220 --> 04:00:49.440
[Guest]: It takes a lot of meaning from games, for example, in lots of games.

04:00:49.440 --> 04:00:54.220
[Guest]: If you are really vested in your character, what is what is called MMORPGs, massively

04:00:54.220 --> 04:00:56.580
[Guest]: multiplayer online role playing games.

04:00:56.580 --> 04:01:00.620
[Guest]: You have various characters that you build over time, they gain experience, they gain

04:01:00.620 --> 04:01:04.660
[Guest]: in these various medieval sort of setting universes.

04:01:04.660 --> 04:01:09.860
[Guest]: They get all these items of clothing or weapons, and you can set them up and you create and

04:01:09.860 --> 04:01:11.700
[Guest]: you give them some kind of value.

04:01:11.700 --> 04:01:14.860
[Guest]: And sometimes you have things that you can pay for.

04:01:14.860 --> 04:01:19.420
[Guest]: You can get this clothing, which is like this, this, this, but you pay $5 for it or you pay

04:01:19.420 --> 04:01:24.140
[Guest]: $10 for it or more like who knows whatever, but do you want to do it?

04:01:24.140 --> 04:01:28.060
[Guest]: It's not really you're not holding it, you're not actually possessing it.

04:01:28.060 --> 04:01:34.260
[Guest]: It's just in this realm, in this game, in this context, in this character, it's virtual.

04:01:34.260 --> 04:01:36.060
[Guest]: But it can have real value, right?

04:01:36.060 --> 04:01:40.020
[Guest]: Like it depends on how much time you spend on that game, how vested you are, how many

04:01:40.020 --> 04:01:44.360
[Guest]: what social networks you have within it, it can have real value to you.

04:01:44.360 --> 04:01:49.980
[Guest]: So if you could buy the blue tick on Twitter, for example, so that has real value, but it's

04:01:49.980 --> 04:01:50.980
[Guest]: a digital thing.

04:01:50.980 --> 04:01:52.380
[Guest]: It's not a real good.

04:01:52.380 --> 04:01:58.500
[Guest]: So if you believe in the idea that virtual worlds can have items that have real monetary

04:01:58.500 --> 04:02:03.620
[Guest]: value, then we are thinking about the ways that we interact with virtual worlds in the

04:02:03.620 --> 04:02:10.140
[Guest]: future and web 3.0 and metaverse and all these ideas are about more and more virtual worlds

04:02:10.140 --> 04:02:18.100
[Guest]: existing in our reality, whether it's virtual reality, whether it's augmented reality, and

04:02:18.100 --> 04:02:23.540
[Guest]: what is the value of getting something over there and flexing it or using it in some way.

04:02:23.540 --> 04:02:27.620
[Guest]: So this is where this is what NFTs offer you in art.

04:02:27.620 --> 04:02:36.260
[Guest]: At the moment, NFTs are or art or writing or audio, NFTs are a way of associating with

04:02:36.260 --> 04:02:42.780
[Guest]: an artist or a writer or a creator that you like because you own something that they have.

04:02:42.780 --> 04:02:44.920
[Guest]: So it's almost like buying a share.

04:02:44.920 --> 04:02:50.420
[Guest]: If someone could buy a share in Amit Verma, that share will always change in value, but

04:02:50.420 --> 04:02:54.260
[Guest]: they buy it with the idea that now they believe in you.

04:02:54.260 --> 04:02:58.140
[Guest]: Now they believe in what you are going to do in the future, and they expect it to appreciate

04:02:58.140 --> 04:02:59.140
[Guest]: in value.

04:02:59.140 --> 04:03:03.820
[Guest]: They might never sell it, but they expect it to not be a money thrown down the drain.

04:03:03.820 --> 04:03:08.980
[Guest]: Meanwhile, that money is money that you can use to become a better artist.

04:03:08.980 --> 04:03:11.020
[Amit Varma]: Okay, so let's look at it like this.

04:03:11.020 --> 04:03:16.220
[Amit Varma]: Let's say I buy a share in a company, I buy a share in a company because there are expectations

04:03:16.220 --> 04:03:20.100
[Amit Varma]: of all its earnings will be like this, these will be the dividends, you know, there'll

04:03:20.100 --> 04:03:23.780
[Amit Varma]: be a resale market for my share, it could go up, it could go down.

04:03:23.780 --> 04:03:28.980
[Amit Varma]: But what I hear a lot about on the internet, and I'm trying to wrap my head around it,

04:03:28.980 --> 04:03:33.380
[Amit Varma]: is that an artist will create an artwork which anyone can see and download, but they sell

04:03:33.380 --> 04:03:35.940
[Amit Varma]: the NFT to it, which one person will buy.

04:03:35.940 --> 04:03:40.940
[Amit Varma]: Now this is a digital artwork, anyone can download copies if they want, and yet one

04:03:40.940 --> 04:03:44.380
[Amit Varma]: person holds and has bought an NFT for it.

04:03:44.380 --> 04:03:48.540
[Amit Varma]: So what special privilege does he get from the NFT apart from having the NFT?

04:03:48.540 --> 04:03:52.740
[Guest]: Yeah, firstly, there's one aspect of the NFT world that says, oh, right clickers, as they

04:03:52.740 --> 04:03:56.700
[Guest]: are called right clickers are evil, and that is don't do it.

04:03:56.700 --> 04:03:58.820
[Guest]: And we need to disable right click.

04:03:58.820 --> 04:04:00.140
[Guest]: Some people are even doing that.

04:04:00.140 --> 04:04:01.140
[Guest]: That's not something I believe in.

04:04:01.140 --> 04:04:02.220
[Guest]: I think that's nonsense.

04:04:02.220 --> 04:04:03.620
[Guest]: That's never going to happen.

04:04:03.620 --> 04:04:06.460
[Guest]: You need to have value outside of this fact.

04:04:06.460 --> 04:04:10.220
[Guest]: Because the internet is not about not letting other people have content.

04:04:10.220 --> 04:04:15.020
[Guest]: Right click save is the essence of a lot of art I have absorbed and learned, you're not

04:04:15.020 --> 04:04:18.540
[Guest]: going to disable right click save, you're not going to disable screenshots and things

04:04:18.540 --> 04:04:21.420
[Guest]: like that, that has to always remain.

04:04:21.420 --> 04:04:25.300
[Guest]: It's the essence of knowledge and the promise of the internet that you are going to have

04:04:25.300 --> 04:04:26.300
[Guest]: this.

04:04:26.300 --> 04:04:29.500
[Guest]: So it has to have some other value in my mind, this kind of value is nonsense, this the demand

04:04:29.500 --> 04:04:31.180
[Guest]: for it is also nonsense.

04:04:31.180 --> 04:04:35.700
[Guest]: But there are there is other value being created around even an NFT of a blog post you wrote,

04:04:35.700 --> 04:04:36.700
[Guest]: for example, right.

04:04:36.700 --> 04:04:40.820
[Guest]: So you have 10,000 blog posts, every week, you write a newsletter post, and every week,

04:04:40.820 --> 04:04:42.940
[Guest]: somebody can buy an NFT of it.

04:04:42.940 --> 04:04:48.380
[Guest]: That thing can does not mean that nobody else gets to read that newsletter, or save that

04:04:48.380 --> 04:04:50.820
[Guest]: newsletter or print that newsletter.

04:04:50.820 --> 04:04:57.420
[Guest]: But within a context, there is a place there is a ledger, where you are acknowledged as

04:04:57.420 --> 04:04:59.380
[Guest]: the owner of that post.

04:04:59.380 --> 04:05:03.100
[Guest]: I suppose I buy that newsletters NFT that posts NFT.

04:05:03.100 --> 04:05:07.460
[Guest]: So I am acknowledged as the owner, there is a list somewhere in which I am there and those

04:05:07.460 --> 04:05:12.020
[Guest]: other right click people are not there, or those savers printers are not there.

04:05:12.020 --> 04:05:15.360
[Guest]: That list can have value if you use it that way.

04:05:15.360 --> 04:05:21.140
[Guest]: So if Amit decides that everybody who owns an Amit NFTs, we are going to all have brunch

04:05:21.140 --> 04:05:27.060
[Guest]: together, I get invited, right, the people who saved it don't get invited, you are incentivizing

04:05:27.060 --> 04:05:31.720
[Guest]: people to buy that NFT, and you are creating value around that NFT.

04:05:31.720 --> 04:05:34.500
[Amit Varma]: But I could achieve the same thing by another mechanism.

04:05:34.500 --> 04:05:38.740
[Amit Varma]: For example, I could say take a Patreon membership and all my members of this particular tier

04:05:38.740 --> 04:05:42.940
[Amit Varma]: get brunch with me and another particular tier gets whatever with me.

04:05:42.940 --> 04:05:47.340
[Amit Varma]: And I could do that also by that I mean, the point is, say I write a blog post and you

04:05:47.340 --> 04:05:51.600
[Amit Varma]: buy the NFT for it, you don't have the copyright for it, you are not going to get revenues

04:05:51.600 --> 04:05:56.340
[Amit Varma]: from it if I publish it in a book or something, you know, you don't stop it from being published,

04:05:56.340 --> 04:05:58.380
[Amit Varma]: you don't stop other people from reading it.

04:05:58.380 --> 04:06:05.660
[Amit Varma]: Although the NFT entitles you to is the ownership of the NFT, which only entitles you to the

04:06:05.660 --> 04:06:09.820
[Amit Varma]: ownership of the NFT, which only we can reach five hours this way.

04:06:09.820 --> 04:06:12.660
[Guest]: And ownership of the NFT on that blockchain.

04:06:12.660 --> 04:06:13.660
[Guest]: Yeah.

