[Guest]: I am not so confident in doing these things.

04:17:26.680 --> 04:17:30.420
[Guest]: Please tell me what you think like me talking just into a mic and telling you a story is

04:17:30.420 --> 04:17:34.980
[Guest]: not something I'm kicked about sharing with my general podcast audience yet.

04:17:34.980 --> 04:17:37.640
[Guest]: But with you, I will because you are my true fans.

04:17:37.640 --> 04:17:41.060
[Guest]: You really care about my work and what I'm another thing I'm doing right now, which has

04:17:41.060 --> 04:17:45.940
[Guest]: been really fun and very gratifying and coming to the point of what you said about blogging

04:17:45.940 --> 04:17:47.380
[Guest]: with an audience.

04:17:47.380 --> 04:17:51.440
[Guest]: So this is a small audience, my insiders, not my broad audience, but I am writing my

04:17:51.440 --> 04:17:52.620
[Guest]: book with them.

04:17:52.620 --> 04:17:56.500
[Guest]: I share passages of my next book, which is going to be sneaky out of Vancouver, and I'm

04:17:56.500 --> 04:18:00.620
[Guest]: going to self publish it, but I'm writing it and I every month I share a new passage

04:18:00.620 --> 04:18:02.140
[Guest]: with them.

04:18:02.140 --> 04:18:05.780
[Guest]: And what this does is it puts me on a monthly schedule every month, I have to have a substantial

04:18:05.780 --> 04:18:08.900
[Guest]: amount written, it has to be about my art, it has to be about Vancouver.

04:18:08.900 --> 04:18:12.660
[Guest]: So I'm incentivized this month to explore Vancouver in some new way, which could add

04:18:12.660 --> 04:18:13.940
[Guest]: to that book.

04:18:13.940 --> 04:18:17.460
[Guest]: And I'm sharing it with this audience that is paying me to read it.

04:18:17.460 --> 04:18:19.660
[Guest]: They are my insiders, they care about my work.

04:18:19.660 --> 04:18:21.420
[Guest]: So they give me excellent feedback.

04:18:21.420 --> 04:18:25.220
[Guest]: They tell me what they like, they tell me what they didn't like, they I'm open to all

04:18:25.220 --> 04:18:28.620
[Guest]: kinds of criticism from them, because I know that they're coming from a they're vested

04:18:28.620 --> 04:18:29.620
[Guest]: in me.

04:18:29.620 --> 04:18:30.620
[Guest]: Right?

04:18:30.620 --> 04:18:34.140
[Guest]: Same similarly about like, you could imagine, oh, if you have people who own your NFTs,

04:18:34.140 --> 04:18:37.780
[Guest]: you know that these people really they are completely vested in you because financially

04:18:37.780 --> 04:18:42.140
[Guest]: they were like NFTs will rise in financial value, the better you do.

04:18:42.140 --> 04:18:46.460
[Guest]: So they are deeply incentivized to ensure your success.

04:18:46.460 --> 04:18:52.140
[Guest]: You are almost recruiting a team to do PR for you also, because they are deeply incentivized

04:18:52.140 --> 04:18:55.980
[Guest]: to always talk about your work, because they own a part of your work, and that will go

04:18:55.980 --> 04:19:01.140
[Guest]: up in value, just like a patron of old, like if they have a painting of yours, it helps

04:19:01.140 --> 04:19:05.060
[Guest]: them if you sell paintings to other people also, because then their painting also goes

04:19:05.060 --> 04:19:08.460
[Guest]: up in value, or you sell painting somewhere else.

04:19:08.460 --> 04:19:13.660
[Guest]: So similarly, with my insiders, I'm playing these little games, which I'm enjoying a lot.

04:19:13.660 --> 04:19:16.540
[Guest]: And they give me feedback, it's useful feedback.

04:19:16.540 --> 04:19:21.540
[Guest]: And it makes me a better writer for my general podcast for my general newsletter, it makes

04:19:21.540 --> 04:19:27.820
[Guest]: me a better thinker, it forces me it incentivizes me to put my thoughts in order.

04:19:27.820 --> 04:19:33.700
[Amit Varma]: And in a year's or six months time, it will lead to a finished book that will be published.

04:19:33.700 --> 04:19:34.700
[Amit Varma]: That's fascinating.

04:19:34.700 --> 04:19:38.580
[Amit Varma]: In fact, I've you know, I've almost by happenstance without thinking too deeply about this stuff

04:19:38.580 --> 04:19:41.420
[Amit Varma]: been kind of successful at building different kinds of communities.

04:19:41.420 --> 04:19:45.380
[Amit Varma]: I mean, there's a clear writing community, obviously, you know, more than 1500 people

04:19:45.380 --> 04:19:48.140
[Amit Varma]: have done the course more than 800 people within that community.

04:19:48.140 --> 04:19:51.580
[Amit Varma]: So got to kind of revitalize that and do more things.

04:19:51.580 --> 04:19:54.540
[Amit Varma]: Plus, there's of course, a few 1000 people who follow my newsletter, even though I've

04:19:54.540 --> 04:19:56.480
[Amit Varma]: posted a handful of times.

